<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>




<p><rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">altar</rs>, originally with moulding below on three sides (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.30</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.69</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.345</measure>); top rough and perhaps intended to carry a crowning feature; hollowed out and re-used as a trough with a circular hole (? for a pipe) cut in the original face.</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on one face.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p><measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.027</measure></p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0129" notAfter="0138" exact="none">129-138 A.D.</date>
(<rs type="criteria">reign</rs>, <rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>)</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>      <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <persName type="emperor"><name reg="Ἁδριανός">Ἁδριανῷ  </name><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="2"/>    <space extent="2" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/> <w lemma="σωτήρ">Σωτῆρι</w> <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="3"/>    <space extent="3" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>    <persName type="divine"><name>Διὶ  </name><space extent="3" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="4"/>    <supplied reason="lost"><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/></supplied>    <w lemma="Ὀκτωβρίων"><supplied reason="lost">Ὀ</supplied>λυμπίῳ</w></persName></persName>  <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="4a"/><space extent="8"/></ab>
</div>


<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>To Hadrian the Saviour Zeus Olympios.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>One of several small 'altars' dedicated to Hadrian:  <xref type="inscription" n="1277" href="090119">9.119</xref> (=81.98), <seg cert="low"><xref type="inscription" n="1266" href="080256">8.256</xref> (=70.254)</seg></p><p>The title Zeus Olympios is thought to follow from the dedication of the Olympieion at Athens in autumn 129.</p><p>The absence of a dedicator's name is unexpected.</p>
</div>
